<worksheet xml:id="ws-Hamilton-2">
  <title>Hamilton's Method Worksheet</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>In this worksheet, you'll practice Hamilton's method for apportionment by working through the Republic of Awoi example.</p>
  </introduction>

  <activity xml:id="hamilton-awoi-practice-2">
    <title>Republic of Awoi - Hamilton's Method</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Consider the Republic of Awoi with four states:
      <ul>
        <li>North-West (NW): population 69,000</li>
        <li>South-West (SW): population 267,000</li> 
        <li>South-East (SE): population 133,000</li>
        <li>North-East (NE): population 331,000</li>
      </ul>
      There are 160 seats to be apportioned.</p>
    </introduction>

    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>Find the standard divisor.</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>Total population = 69,000 + 267,000 + 133,000 + 331,000 = 800,000</p>
        <p>Standard divisor = 800,000 ÷ 160 = 5,000</p>
      </solution>
    </task>

