  <assemblage xml:id="hamilton-method-steps-2">
    <title>Hamilton's Method - Step by Step</title>
    <ol>
      <li><p>Calculate the total population</p></li>
      <li><p>Identify the number of seats to be apportioned</p></li>
      <li><p>Calculate the Standard Divisor (total population ÷ number of seats)</p></li>
      <li><p>Calculate all Standard Quotas (each state's population ÷ Standard Divisor). 
          The total of standard quotas should equal the number of seats.</p></li>
      <li><p>Find all Lower Quotas by dropping the decimal parts. 
          The total of lower quotas should be less than the number of seats.</p></li>
      <li><p>Distribute additional seats by giving one seat to each state with the largest decimal parts 
          until all seats are assigned.</p></li>
    </ol>
  </assemblage>
